[1] India (Haryana)
[2] UK

******
[1] India (Haryana)
Date: Tue 19 Jan 2010
Source: Press Trust of India (PTI) [edited]
<http://www.ptinews.com/news/475718_Agri-scientists-warn-farmers-against-yellow-rust>


Agri scientists warn farmers against yellow rust
------------------------------------------------
Agricultural scientists have warned farmers against yellow rust, an
infectious and windborne disease affecting wheat crops. Growth of the
infected plants is weakened and stunted which causes nearly 50 per cent
loss of production, Haryana Agricultural University's Dr RP Narwal said.

"Yellow rust develops rapidly when free moisture occurs and temperatures
range between 10-20 deg C [50-68 deg F]. Primarily this disease occurs in
wheat crop grown in cooler climates, which are generally associated with
higher elevations and northern latitudes. The leaves of infected crop
produce yellow coloured stripes," he said.

